Tucson still holds his ground, despite the dinosaur's charge.  As they near=
 him, he rears up, extends his enormous wings and beats them with powerful =
thrusts, hoping to create enough wind resistance to keep them at bay.  His =
tail whips around in powerful coils as he prepares to catch one of them wit=
h a constrictor grip, in an attempt to slow them down.   He sees something =
very familiar about them, yet having had a portion of his memory erased whe=
n Cyclonus struck him vorns ago, he could not really be sure he was seeing =
who he thought he was seeing.  His expression changes, as anger is replaced=
 by confusion and anticipation.  

" Grimlock?  Wait!  Is your name Grimloc=
k?"   

Tucson shows the leader his Maximal faction symbol, and a small Aut=
obot symbol located on his left front haunch.

" I am Tucson Prime, formall=
y Tucson!  You might have known me in my Autobot alt form!  But I assure yo=
u that I'm not lying!   I once worked for Optimus Prime!  "

He hoped that =
Grimlock would sort of remember who he was.  He then takes a submissive sta=
nce, showing that he means no harm.

Perpetually on the move and constantly=
 busy.
